Polymetal Plunges Most in Seven Weeks as Gold and Silver Decline

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-26T07:08:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/polymetal-plunges-most-in-seven-weeks-as-gold-and-silver-decline.html
OAO Polymetal, the Russian silver
and gold producer, recorded its biggest intraday fall in seven
weeks as both metals tumbled.  Its shares slid as much as 9.2 percent, the biggest
intraday fall since Aug. 5, and last traded 7.8 percent lower by
10:58 a.m. in Moscow.  Cash gold fell as much as 3.1 percent to a two-month low of
$1,604.85 an ounce. The metal fell 4.8 percent on Sept. 23, the
most since Dec. 1, 2008. Spot silver lost as much as 9.9 percent
to $28.0525 an ounce.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  